1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about open data replication than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:10,400
Open data replication means sharing research data openly, allowing anyone to verify results.

3
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,800
Yet, many studies struggle with reproducibility.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:13,200
Why?

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,800
Research shows around 50% of studies can’t be replicated.

6
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:19,600
This isn't due to fraud but complexity.

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:22,800
And unlike social media hype, science demands scrutiny.

8
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:27,200
Open data can strengthen trust and lead to better health outcomes.

9
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,800
It’s a game changer.

10
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:33,200
Follow for more insights on how open data can transform science!
